article.headline: James Madison 58, Towson 56
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- Humpty Hitchens scored 18 points and Devon Moore made four free throws in the final 30 seconds to help James Madison beat Towson 58-56 Saturday. Hitchens hit five 3-pointers en route to 6 of 9 shooting for the Dukes, who snapped a five-game losing skid. James Madison (11-16, 4-11 Colonial Athletic Association) started hot, opening the game on a 25-8 run and taking a 36-21 lead into halftime behind an Andrey Semenov layup. Towson (1-26, 1-14) rallied in the second half to take its first lead of the game, 51-49, with 3:20 left to play but Hitchens made a trey and Moore scored the Dukes' final six points to seal the win. Despite dominating the boards 49-19 the Tigers shot just 27.6 percent (16 of 58) from the field. James Madison shot 45.5 percent (10 of 22) from 3-point range. Robert Nwankwo led Towson with 15 points and 15 rebounds.
